      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ أُمِّ اَلْوَلَدِ قَالَ \"أَمَةٌ تُبَاعُ وَ تُورَثُ وَ تُوهَبُ وَ حَدُّهَا حَدُّ اَلْأَمَةِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3507 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Ali ibn Ri'ab, from Zurara, who said:\nI asked Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), about Umm al-Walad (a female slave who bears a child for her master).\nImam (as) said: \"She is a slave. She can be sold, inherited, and gifted, and her legal ruling is the same as that of a slave.\""
        ]
      }
    },
